-- Falcons Beat Panthers to Improve to NFL-Best 11-2 Record; Steelers Win
-- B y   D e x   M c L u s k e y
-- 2010-12-12T21:01:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-12/falcons-beat-panthers-to-improve-to-nfl-best-11-2-record-steelers-win.html
The Atlanta Falcons beat the
Carolina Panthers 31-10 to improve to 11-2 for the season, the
best record in the National Football League.  Also in Week 14, the Pittsburgh Steelers won their fourth
straight game and sent the Cincinnati Bengals to a 10th
consecutive loss. Pittsburgh won 23-7 to improve to 10-3.  Later today, the New England Patriots can join the Falcons
at 11-2 with a victory at the Chicago Bears.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dex McLuskey at 
 dmcluskey@bloomberg.net  